            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Eumenis"><name nymRef="#Εὐμενίς"><expan><abbr>Ε<unclear>ὐ</unclear></abbr><ex>μενίδων</ex></expan></name></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Autel</supplied> des Euménides.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altar</supplied> of the Eumenides.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altare</supplied> delle Eumenidi.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>(يفهم ضمنياً بأنه مذبح) لإفمينديس</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>Due to the conditions of quick survey it was not possible for E. Rosamilia to clean the altar and check the predictable two compartments. However the 
               placement of the abbreviated name of the Eumenides helps to suppose that there were two of them.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
